In the hope that it would be possible to send you the money

                collected for the Bible and the “Occident”, I postponed my writing to you
 from
                week to week. The punishment for my waiting is that in spite of the
 efforts,
                the success is a very insignificant one. The following of your
 subscribers are
                already in possession of your work, and i beg of you to
 take notice of this:
                    Emanuel Lieberman, $8.; M. L. Sale,
                $10.; S. Bamberger, $8.;

                G. I. Jessel, $10.; Emanuel Bamberger,
                $10.; S. Ullman, $10.; L. Lowenson, $8.;

                M. Straus, $12.; Abraham Dinkelspiel, Jr.,
                $10.; A. Dinkelspiel, $8.; Jacob

                    Wurzburger, $10; Ch.Lichten, $10.;
                    S.Maas, $8.; H. Seliger, 8.;
                    S.Bach, 8.;

